<class module="niagaraDriver" runtimeProfile="rt" qualifiedName="com.tridium.nd.sysdef.BReachableStations" name="BReachableStations" packageName="com.tridium.nd.sysdef" public="true" final="true">
<description>
BReachableStations is a container of &lt;code&gt;<see ref="com.tridium.nd.sysdef.BReachableStationInfo">BReachableStationInfo</see>&lt;/code&gt; instances&#xa; which describe all of the downstream NiagaraStations that are reachable from&#xa; the parent &lt;code&gt;<see ref="com.tridium.nd.BNiagaraStation">BNiagaraStation</see>&lt;/code&gt; in which this container resides.&#xa; It has an action to update the reachable, downstream NiagaraStations and&#xa; model them as child &lt;code&gt;<see ref="com.tridium.nd.sysdef.BReachableStationInfo">BReachableStationInfo</see>&lt;/code&gt; instances.
</description>
<tag name="@author">Scott Hoye on 05/06/2021</tag>
<tag name="@since">Niagara 4.13</tag>
<extends>
<type class="javax.baja.driver.util.BAbstractDescriptor"/>
</extends>
<implements>
<type class="javax.baja.util.BIRestrictedComponent"/>
</implements>
<implements>
<type class="com.tridium.fox.sys.BFoxClientConnection$Interest"/>
</implements>
<action name="updateReachableStations" flags="ca">
<parameter name="parameter">
<type class="javax.baja.sys.BBoolean"/>
</parameter>
<return>
<type class="void"/>
</return>
<description>
Slot for the &lt;code&gt;updateReachableStations&lt;/code&gt; action.&#xa; Perform a downstream, cascading query and update the child&#xa; BReachableStationInfo instances on this container. The boolean parameter&#xa; specifies whether to keep any existing child BReachableStationInfo instances&#xa; and only add new ones or to update all child BReachableStationInfo instances,&#xa; which also means removing any that are no longer detected as reachable during&#xa; this query.
</description>
<tag name="@see">#updateReachableStations(BBoolean parameter)</tag>
</action>

</class>
</bajadoc>
